a person, they find a guy,

00:03:14.310 --> 00:03:17.880 align:middle line:84%
they find a woman who has a
conviction and go with it.

00:03:17.880 --> 00:03:19.560 align:middle line:84%
So what I try and
do is say, well,

00:03:19.560 --> 00:03:22.950 align:middle line:84%
let's use some of the
tools of philosophy, so

00:03:22.950 --> 00:03:26.960 align:middle line:84%
the study of being, ontology,
and the study of knowledge,

00:03:26.960 --> 00:03:30.270 align:middle line:84%
epistemology, and
try and determine

00:03:30.270 --> 00:03:32.360 align:middle line:90%
how it is we know something.

00:03:32.360 --> 00:03:33.529 align:middle line:90%
How do we know a thing?

00:03:33.529 --> 00:03:34.820 align:middle line:90%
How do we actually get to that?

00:03:34.820 --> 00:03:39.480 align:middle line:84%
So if you went to
your philosophy class

00:03:39.480 --> 00:03:43.690 align:middle line:84%
101 at university and
you went on the first day

00:03:43.690 --> 00:03:46.660 align:middle line:84%
to look at epistemology,
they would say, well,

00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:48.810 align:middle line:90%
let's give you an example.

00:03:48.810 --> 00:03:50.020 align:middle line:90%
What is the sun?

00:03:50.020 --> 00:03:55.210 align:middle line:84%
And people would say, well,
it's a giant fireball.

00:03:55.210 --> 00:03:57.470 align:middle line:90%
We all revolve around it.

00:03:57.470 --> 00:04:01.232 align:middle line:84%
And it's about 93 million
miles away from the Earth.

00:04:01.232 --> 00:04:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And the teacher, the
professor would say, well,

00:04:03.190 --> 00:04:04.495 align:middle line:90%
how do you know that?

00:04:04.495 --> 00:04:05.950 align:middle line:90%
How do you know that?

00:04:05.950 --> 00:04:06.860 align:middle line:90%
How do you know that?

00:04:06.860 --> 00:04:11.590 align:middle line:84%
You'd say, well, some scientists
have measured it with radar.

00:04:11.590 --> 00:04:15.020 align:middle line:84%
They can determine the
distance of Venus and the sun

00:04:15.020 --> 00:04:18.209 align:middle line:84%
and thereby extrapolate
the distance from-- but how

00:04:18.209 --> 00:04:19.084 align:middle line:90%
do you know that?

00:04:19.084 --> 00:04:20.750 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is,
they don't know that.

00:04:20.750 --> 00:04:22.210 align:middle line:90%
Somebody told them.

00:04:22.210 --> 00:04:23.900 align:middle line:84%
So even the most
basic thing that we

00:04:23.900 --> 00:04:25.880 align:middle line:84%
have every single
day, the sun, we

00:04:25.880 --> 00:04:28.580 align:middle line:84%
don't actually know
personally what it is.

00:04:28.580 --> 00:04:32.570 align:middle line:84%
We just have this knowledge
that has been passed to us.

00:04:32.570 --> 00:04:36.690 align:middle line:84%
But there's no personal
experiential knowledge of it.

00:04:36.690 --> 00:04:39.140 align:middle line:84%
So you know, the professor
would go around the class

00:04:39.140 --> 00:04:41.080 align:middle line:84%
and give examples
of all these things.

00:04:41.080 --> 00:04:42.970 align:middle line:90%
What is the moon?

00:04:42.970 --> 00:04:44.200 align:middle line:90%
What happens after you die?

00:04:44.200 --> 00:04:45.750 align:middle line:90%
And nobody knows anything.

00:04:45.750 --> 00:04:48.080 align:middle line:84%
So there's just this
established idea

00:04:48.080 --> 00:04:51.540 align:middle line:84%
that most of what we
classify as knowledge

00:04:51.540 --> 00:04:54.090 align:middle line:90%
is in fact just belief.

00:04:54.090 --> 00:04:55.040 align:middle line:90%
It's just belief.

00:04:55.040 --> 00:04:57.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You know, there's
something interesting,

00:04:57.290 --> 00:05:03.260 align:middle line:84%
because as you brought up, the
parapolitical/conspiracy age,

00:05:03.260 --> 00:05:06.550 align:middle line:84%
I think that there
was such a deep schism

00:05:06.550 --> 00:05:08.690 align:middle line:90%
in the psyche of humanity.

00:05:08.690 --> 00:05:12.690 align:middle line:84%
It's like to use it as
just a simple example,

00:05:12.690 --> 00:05:16.260 align:middle line:84%
say you suspect your wife's
cheating on you, right?

00:05:16.260 --> 00:05:17.690 align:middle line:90%
You can feel it.

00:05:17.690 --> 00:05:21.890 align:middle line:84%
It's just clawing at the back
of your emotions and your mind.

00:05:21.890 --> 00:05:24.370 align:middle line:84%
You feel it, but you don't
have the evidence yet.

00:05:24.370 --> 00:05:27.400 align:middle line:84%
As soon as you jump on
a piece of what appears

00:05:27.400 --> 00:05:28.990 align:middle line:90%
to be solid evidence, boom.

00:05:28.990 --> 00:05:31.800 align:middle line:84%
You have a whole new philosophy
and belief about what

00:05:31.800 --> 00:05:32.790 align:middle line:90%
happened there.

00:05:32.790 --> 00:05:34.930 align:middle line:84%
And I think the cognitive
dissonance and mass

00:05:34.930 --> 00:05:38.180 align:middle line:84%
of knowing we've been lied
to through so many systems

00:05:38.180 --> 00:05:41.710 align:middle line:84%
for so long, just feeling
split, uncomfortable, not

00:05:41.710 --> 00:05:44.450 align:middle line:84%
able to really take control
of our will and our thoughts

00:05:44.450 --> 00:05:47.730 align:middle line:84%
properly anymore,
conspiracy came along

00:05:47.730 --> 00:05:50.560 align:middle line:84%
I think to fill a gap,
which is, OK, here

00:05:50.560 --> 00:05:52.320 align:middle line:90%
are some other ideas about it.

00:05:52.320 --> 00:05:55.890 align:middle line:84%
And so people jumped on
that as a belief system

00:05:55.890 --> 00:05:58.200 align:middle line:84%
and without questioning
a lot of stuff,

00:05:58.200 --> 00:06:01.260 align:middle line:84%
because it satisfied
that discomfort

00:06:01.260 --> 00:06:03.632 align:middle line:84%
of the cognitive dissonance
of knowing you're lied to

00:06:03.632 --> 00:06:05.340 align:middle line:84%
and you're off-kilter
but don't know why.

00:06:05.340 --> 00:06:06.220 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:06:06.220 --> 00:06:10.090 align:middle line:84%
And I think that panders to
the human impulse and desire

00:06:10.090 --> 00:06:14.800 align:middle line:84%
to want to follow, so I
think it's extremely unusual

00:06:14.800 --> 00:06:19.270 align:middle line:84%
to get self-determining human
beings who want to discriminate

00:06:19.270 --> 00:06:20.800 align:middle line:90%
and make judgments.

00:06:20.800 --> 00:06:23.855 align:middle line:84%
You know, these days it's
very unfashionable to judge,

00:06:23.855 --> 00:06:24.655 align:middle line:90%
isn't it?

00:06:24.655 --> 00:06:26.863 align:middle line:84%
You hear a lot of people
saying, oh, I'm not judging.

00:06:26.863 --> 00:06:28.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm not judging.

00:06:28.210 --> 00:06:29.970 align:middle line:90%
I have no problem with judging.

00:06:29.970 --> 00:06:30.890 align:middle line:90%
Judge away.

00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:34.590 align:middle line:84%
You have to make a quality call,
basically, say this is rubbish

00:06:34.590 --> 00:06:35.574 align:middle line:90%
and this is excellent.

00:06:35.574 --> 00:06:37.740 align:middle line:84%
And in the middle, there's
something that's average,

00:06:37.740 --> 00:06:39.310 align:middle line:90%
and that's OK.

00:06:39.310 --> 00:06:40.880 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
sort of judgement

00:06:40.880 --> 00:06:44.250 align:middle line:84%
you can make for yourself,
so most people don't want

00:06:44.250 --> 00:06:46.920 align:middle line:84%
to self-determine, because
it means they have to become

00:06:46.920 --> 00:06:50.034 align:middle line:84%
their own authority, so they'd
rather have someone else do it.

00:06:50.034 --> 00:06:51.575 align:middle line:84%
And I think when
people do understand

00:06:51.575 --> 00:06:56.060 align:middle line:84%
that the government isn't
really what we thought

00:06:56.060 --> 00:06:59.370 align:middle line:84%
it was when we were children and
the United Nations isn't what

00:06:59.370 --> 00:07:03.590 align:middle line:84%
we thought it was and a lot
of major wars in Vietnam

00:07:03.590 --> 00:07:06.190 align:middle line:84%
and World War II and
Iraq, they're not

00:07:06.190 --> 00:07:08.660 align:middle line:84%
what we thought they were
and the Federal Reserve

00:07:08.660 --> 00:07:10.350 align:middle line:84%
isn't what we-- and
so on and so on.

00:07:10.350 --> 00:07:16.260 align:middle line:84%
And you realize that what
we'd invested in our belief

00:07:16.260 --> 00:07:19.320 align:middle line:84%
has been disrespected
and dishonored.

00:07:19.320 --> 00:07:22.480 align:middle line:84%
Then you immediately want an
honorable thing to follow.

00:07:22.480 --> 00:07:24.127 align:middle line:84%
So the first guy
who comes along--

00:07:24.127 --> 00:07:25.085 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's right.

00:07:25.085 --> 00:07:28.340 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --who has any sort of
half-conviction and who looks

00:07:28.340 --> 00:07:29.140 align:middle line:90%
honorable--

00:07:29.140 --> 00:07:30.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A shred
of evidence, even.

00:07:30.620 --> 00:07:32.495 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --and who has
some information that

00:07:32.495 --> 00:07:34.790 align:middle line:84%
could be considered
as Plato described it

00:07:34.790 --> 00:07:37.480 align:middle line:90%
as justified true belief.

00:07:37.480 --> 00:07:40.770 align:middle line:84%
That's knowledge, it doesn't
have to be fact and universally

00:07:40.770 --> 00:07:43.150 align:middle line:84%
applicable, just
a true belief that

00:07:43.150 --> 00:07:46.740 align:middle line:84%
is justified for one's
self, then they follow it.

00:07:46.740 --> 00:07:49.370 align:middle line:84%
So a question I get
asked all the time, which

00:07:49.370 --> 00:07:52.910 align:middle line:84%
is why I raised this considering
what to talk to you about

00:07:52.910 --> 00:07:55.610 align:middle line:84%
today, people say
to me all the time,

00:07:55.610 --> 00:07:57.450 align:middle line:90%
how do I know who to follow?

00:07:57.450 --> 00:07:59.720 align:middle line:84%
This guy says things and
it's really interesting,

00:07:59.720 --> 00:08:03.440 align:middle line:84%
loads of followers, big
numbers, great stuff, but--

00:08:03.440 --> 00:08:04.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Intriguing.

00:08:04.430 --> 00:08:05.240 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: It's intriguing.

00:08:05.240 --> 00:08:06.040 align:middle line:90%
It's juicy.

00:08:06.040 --> 00:08:09.030 align:middle line:90%
It's salacious sometimes.

00:08:09.030 --> 00:08:09.830 align:middle line:90%
Is that wrong?

00:08:09.830 --> 00:08:11.420 align:middle line:90%
Is that rubbish or is it good?

00:08:11.420 --> 00:08:13.270 align:middle line:84%
You know, is there
something to learn?

00:08:13.270 --> 00:08:14.610 align:middle line:90%
How can we tell?

00:08:14.610 --> 00:08:19.270 align:middle line:84%
And my answer is, well,
experiential knowledge

00:08:19.270 --> 00:08:21.130 align:middle line:84%
is the only real
primary one, so you

00:08:21.130 --> 00:08:23.160 align:middle line:90%
have to do that for yourself.

00:08:23.160 --> 00:08:27.250 align:middle line:84%
But also in the character
of the individual

00:08:27.250 --> 00:08:30.910 align:middle line:84%
and in the sort of
comportment of the individual

00:08:30.910 --> 00:08:34.289 align:middle line:84%
there's a lot of clues, so you
can tell things straight away.

00:08:34.289 --> 00:08:35.730 align:middle line:90%
So I've said this to you--

00:08:35.730 --> 00:08:37.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Don't
ignore the clues.

00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:37.650 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Don't
ignore the clues.

00:08:37.650 --> 00:08:39.260 align:middle line:84%
I've said this to
you off-camera,

00:08:39.260 --> 00:08:42.929 align:middle line:84%
but I think we're quite safe
to say it on-camera as well.

00:08:42.929 --> 00:08:45.290 align:middle line:84%
You know, I've followed
people in the past myself,

00:08:45.290 --> 00:08:49.090 align:middle line:84%
the work, and read books and
been to conferences and that.

00:08:49.090 --> 00:08:51.310 align:middle line:84%
And then I've gone to
a conference to speak.

00:08:51.310 --> 00:08:52.395 align:middle line:90%
And this guy's coming.

00:08:52.395 --> 00:08:53.270 align:middle line:90%
I thought, oh, great.

00:08:53.270 --> 00:08:54.149 align:middle line:90%
This guy.

00:08:54.149 --> 00:08:55.440 align:middle line:90%
I've always wanted to meet him.

00:08:55.440 --> 00:08:56.490 align:middle line:90%
His work is great.

00:08:56.490 --> 00:08:57.860 align:middle line:90%
And then I meet him.

00:08:57.860 --> 00:09:00.370 align:middle line:84%
And he's-- well,
let's put it politely.

00:09:00.370 --> 00:09:01.990 align:middle line:90%
He's not who I thought he was.

00:09:01.990 --> 00:09:05.755 align:middle line:84%
And then offstage, you know,
the behavior is different.

00:09:05.755 --> 00:09:08.590 align:middle line:84%
And I'm just thinking,
so it's just something

00:09:08.590 --> 00:09:12.154 align:middle line:90%
that you do as a presentation.

00:09:12.154 --> 00:09:13.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's an
idea that sells.

00:09:13.570 --> 00:09:15.680 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: It's a
version of yourself

00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:18.490 align:middle line:84%
that you've put forward, but
it's not really integrated.

00:09:18.490 --> 00:09:21.190 align:middle line:84%
It's not really
transformed in yourself.

00:09:21.190 --> 00:09:23.700 align:middle line:84%
So the point of
experiential knowledge

00:09:23.700 --> 00:09:27.185 align:middle line:84%
is it is transformative,
so a line I sometimes use

00:09:27.185 --> 00:09:31.020 align:middle line:84%
is truth destroys the
world you used to live in.

00:09:31.020 --> 00:09:31.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:09:31.820 --> 00:09:33.650 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: And when
that happens, people

00:09:33.650 --> 00:09:36.640 align:middle line:84%
are so desperate to
cling on to something new

00:09:36.640 --> 00:09:42.000 align:middle line:84%
that they want just our belief
system to replace it with.

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:45.420 align:middle line:84%
So what I often
suggest to people is

00:09:45.420 --> 00:09:47.970 align:middle line:84%
