00:09:47.970 --> 00:09:51.594 align:middle line:84%
to just be in this like
void, in this limbo where you

00:09:51.594 --> 00:09:52.760 align:middle line:90%
don't know what anything is.

00:09:52.760 --> 00:09:53.560 align:middle line:90%
There's no yes.

00:09:53.560 --> 00:09:55.730 align:middle line:84%
There's no no, no
left and right.

00:09:55.730 --> 00:09:57.150 align:middle line:90%
It's not clear what anything is.

00:09:57.150 --> 00:10:00.900 align:middle line:84%
And as-- I don't want to quote
old philosophers all the time,

00:10:00.900 --> 00:10:03.220 align:middle line:84%
but I was talking about
this the other day.

00:10:03.220 --> 00:10:06.480 align:middle line:84%
Socrates said, until you
accept that you know nothing,

00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:08.420 align:middle line:90%
you can't see truth.

00:10:08.420 --> 00:10:10.890 align:middle line:84%
So there is a
fundamental naivety that

00:10:10.890 --> 00:10:13.594 align:middle line:90%
has to be sort of re-embraced.

00:10:13.594 --> 00:10:17.040 align:middle line:84%
And the great Zen
teacher Shunryu Suzuki

00:10:17.040 --> 00:10:20.900 align:middle line:84%
said in the beginner's mind
there are many possibilities,

00:10:20.900 --> 00:10:23.590 align:middle line:84%
and in the expert
mind there are few.

00:10:23.590 --> 00:10:25.150 align:middle line:84%
So the beginner's
mind is something

00:10:25.150 --> 00:10:28.670 align:middle line:84%
we can cultivate,
even as mature adults

00:10:28.670 --> 00:10:30.610 align:middle line:84%
and as people with
lots of knowledge

00:10:30.610 --> 00:10:31.960 align:middle line:90%
and lots of experiences.

00:10:31.960 --> 00:10:35.370 align:middle line:84%
But that willingness
to be flexible and say,

00:10:35.370 --> 00:10:38.120 align:middle line:84%
well, I don't know
what the sun is.

00:10:38.120 --> 00:10:41.610 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
happened at Sandy Hook

00:10:41.610 --> 00:10:43.380 align:middle line:84%
with apparently
this young man who

00:10:43.380 --> 00:10:45.110 align:middle line:90%
went and killed a lot of kids.

00:10:45.110 --> 00:10:47.050 align:middle line:90%
I'm not sure about that.

00:10:47.050 --> 00:10:49.900 align:middle line:84%
And I know that there's
something wrong,

00:10:49.900 --> 00:10:53.230 align:middle line:84%
but I don't need to immediately
pin my colors to anything.

00:10:53.230 --> 00:10:56.140 align:middle line:84%
I'm happy to just--
it's not a yes.

00:10:56.140 --> 00:10:56.940 align:middle line:90%
It's not a no.

00:10:56.940 --> 00:10:59.972 align:middle line:84%
It's in a neutral file,
with just a big Dr.

00:10:59.972 --> 00:11:01.645 align:middle line:90%
Who question mark on it.

00:11:01.645 --> 00:11:03.770 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But people have
so much of their identity

00:11:03.770 --> 00:11:06.870 align:middle line:84%
wrapped up in their beliefs
and their alliances.

00:11:06.870 --> 00:11:09.880 align:middle line:84%
And it really seems
to be the challenge.

00:11:09.880 --> 00:11:10.680 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: It is.

00:11:10.680 --> 00:11:16.880 align:middle line:84%
Belief is like partially
responsible for formulating

00:11:16.880 --> 00:11:22.340 align:middle line:84%
identity, so in most people's
life we all come to the point

00:11:22.340 --> 00:11:26.790 align:middle line:84%
where perhaps we realize
that Santa Claus,

00:11:26.790 --> 00:11:28.790 align:middle line:84%
or an England Father
Christmas we called him--

00:11:28.790 --> 00:11:30.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, that
was a sad day.

00:11:30.890 --> 00:11:32.580 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: --is like not a thing.

00:11:32.580 --> 00:11:35.837 align:middle line:84%
It's an idea and it's
based on a real guy

00:11:35.837 --> 00:11:37.920 align:middle line:84%
and that's based on somebody
and that was actually

00:11:37.920 --> 00:11:39.400 align:middle line:90%
based on Odin of all people.

00:11:39.400 --> 00:11:43.450 align:middle line:84%
But there comes a point
where you realize that that

00:11:43.450 --> 00:11:45.820 align:middle line:90%
affects your sense of identity.

00:11:45.820 --> 00:11:49.230 align:middle line:84%
So I remember a young man
when I was a kid and he said,

00:11:49.230 --> 00:11:50.260 align:middle line:90%
have you found out yet?

00:11:50.260 --> 00:11:51.385 align:middle line:90%
And I said, found out what?

00:11:51.385 --> 00:11:53.540 align:middle line:84%
And he said, there's
no Father Christmas.

00:11:53.540 --> 00:11:55.360 align:middle line:90%
And I said no, not yet.

00:11:55.360 --> 00:11:57.660 align:middle line:84%
And you know, he was
giving me a heads-up.

00:11:57.660 --> 00:11:58.860 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, I
don't think there is.

00:11:58.860 --> 00:12:00.165 align:middle line:84%
He said, you'll have to
make your own mind up,

00:12:00.165 --> 00:12:02.414 align:middle line:84%
but I don't think there is,
because he was only young,

00:12:02.414 --> 00:12:03.900 align:middle line:90%
but he was a year older than me.

00:12:03.900 --> 00:12:06.360 align:middle line:84%
And I just thought,
well, that's crazy,

00:12:06.360 --> 00:12:08.830 align:middle line:84%
because that's the
whole excitement for me

00:12:08.830 --> 00:12:11.390 align:middle line:84%
was that this mystical
figure would come down

00:12:11.390 --> 00:12:13.300 align:middle line:84%
the chimney in the
house, magically--

00:12:13.300 --> 00:12:14.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah.

00:12:14.100 --> 00:12:15.952 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --and
put gifts, and how

00:12:15.952 --> 00:12:18.160 align:middle line:84%
he got a bicycle down the
chimney, I always wondered.

00:12:18.160 --> 00:12:23.420 align:middle line:84%
But you know, it was a magical
thing, but from that point,

00:12:23.420 --> 00:12:27.170 align:middle line:84%
I think most people then come
to question beliefs, as a child.

00:12:27.170 --> 00:12:29.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, but
there's something built

00:12:29.390 --> 00:12:31.290 align:middle line:90%
in psychologically in that.

00:12:31.290 --> 00:12:33.780 align:middle line:84%
And as it's said that
a cynic is simply

00:12:33.780 --> 00:12:38.050 align:middle line:84%
a broken-hearted dreamer, that
may start with the revelation

00:12:38.050 --> 00:12:39.820 align:middle line:90%
that Santa Claus is not real.

00:12:39.820 --> 00:12:43.020 align:middle line:84%
And people respond to this
information very differently.

00:12:43.020 --> 00:12:46.090 align:middle line:84%
Some try to replace it with
something else as magical.

00:12:46.090 --> 00:12:47.460 align:middle line:90%
Other people say, that's it.

00:12:47.460 --> 00:12:49.520 align:middle line:84%
I'm not believing
any of it anymore.

00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:52.430 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting what happens
psychologically with being,

00:12:52.430 --> 00:12:55.600 align:middle line:84%
quote, "deceived" for
the best of intentions

00:12:55.600 --> 00:12:57.450 align:middle line:84%
on these early
childhood stories.

00:12:57.450 --> 00:12:57.760 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: It is.

00:12:57.760 --> 00:12:59.884 align:middle line:84%
Well, it was interesting
for me because I found out

00:12:59.884 --> 00:13:04.560 align:middle line:84%
that as I say Santa Claus was
based on this Norse figure who

00:13:04.560 --> 00:13:06.190 align:middle line:84%
was actually very
magical and was

00:13:06.190 --> 00:13:10.760 align:middle line:84%
this great figure
of transformation

00:13:10.760 --> 00:13:11.860 align:middle line:90%
and transmutation.

00:13:11.860 --> 00:13:14.320 align:middle line:84%
So as it happened, just
like 10 years later,

00:13:14.320 --> 00:13:16.945 align:middle line:84%
I discovered an even
more magical figure

00:13:16.945 --> 00:13:18.140 align:middle line:90%
who he was based on.

00:13:18.140 --> 00:13:21.896 align:middle line:84%
So for me, it never was
disintegrated, you know.

00:13:21.896 --> 00:13:23.810 align:middle line:84%
But I think for a
lot of people, they

00:13:23.810 --> 00:13:25.380 align:middle line:90%
need something to believe in.

00:13:25.380 --> 00:13:26.910 align:middle line:90%
They need something to grasp.

00:13:26.910 --> 00:13:28.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we need
that magical quality,

00:13:28.970 --> 00:13:30.680 align:middle line:84%
that metaphysical,
magical quality.

00:13:30.680 --> 00:13:31.480 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:13:31.480 --> 00:13:37.550 align:middle line:84%
And even the most conservative
sort of Republicans or whatnot

00:13:37.550 --> 00:13:41.820 align:middle line:84%
who maybe go to church and
need a very practical view,

00:13:41.820 --> 00:13:45.760 align:middle line:84%
they still have their
version of that magical thing

00:13:45.760 --> 00:13:47.970 align:middle line:84%
and some sort of
transcendental quality.

00:13:47.970 --> 00:13:52.020 align:middle line:84%
So I think what
I'm putting forward

00:13:52.020 --> 00:13:56.740 align:middle line:84%
by examining stuff in the
epistemological sense of what

00:13:56.740 --> 00:13:59.800 align:middle line:84%
is knowledge, how do you
determine what it is, it moves

00:13:59.800 --> 00:14:02.160 align:middle line:84%
you not to just
deconstruct and make it

00:14:02.160 --> 00:14:05.490 align:middle line:84%
all very bland and gray,
but quite the reverse.

00:14:05.490 --> 00:14:08.230 align:middle line:84%
It gets you to say, well, this
is quite an exciting thing,

00:14:08.230 --> 00:14:11.200 align:middle line:84%
because nobody really
is sure of anything.

00:14:11.200 --> 00:14:13.330 align:middle line:84%
Even things like we
know black holes,

00:14:13.330 --> 00:14:15.390 align:middle line:84%
we don't know that
they're a thing.

00:14:15.390 --> 00:14:17.500 align:middle line:84%
Atoms, that's a
theoretical thing.

00:14:17.500 --> 00:14:18.740 align:middle line:90%
We don't know that's a thing.

00:14:18.740 --> 00:14:21.420 align:middle line:84%
Electricity, nobody
knows what that is.

00:14:21.420 --> 00:14:24.170 align:middle line:84%
We know how it functions,
but we don't know what it is.

00:14:24.170 --> 00:14:25.860 align:middle line:84%
So things that are
around us every day

00:14:25.860 --> 00:14:29.620 align:middle line:84%
that most people think are
real things are not actually

00:14:29.620 --> 00:14:31.490 align:middle line:90%
anything other than ideas.

00:14:31.490 --> 00:14:36.540 align:middle line:84%
And if you push very empirical
materialist scientists on that,

00:14:36.540 --> 00:14:38.410 align:middle line:84%
they'll go, well,
yeah, that's true.

00:14:38.410 --> 00:14:39.770 align:middle line:90%
No one's ever seen a black hole.

00:14:39.770 --> 00:14:43.680 align:middle line:84%
We posit them and we
posit an atomic structure,

00:14:43.680 --> 00:14:45.910 align:middle line:90%
but they're not actually things.

00:14:45.910 --> 00:14:47.250 align:middle line:90%
It's an idea.

00:14:47.250 --> 00:14:49.080 align:middle line:84%
And as I say,
electricity, same thing.

00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:50.790 align:middle line:90%
It's like, wow, wait a minute.

00:14:50.790 --> 00:14:54.320 align:middle line:84%
So the sun and the moon,
electricity, all these things

00:14:54.320 --> 00:14:58.280 align:middle line:84%
around us, we're not sure
exactly what they are,

00:14:58.280 --> 00:14:59.670 align:middle line:90%
they're just ideas.

00:14:59.670 --> 00:15:01.445 align:middle line:90%
To me, that's very exciting.

00:15:01.445 --> 00:15:01.832 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yet we
have an experience

00:15:01.832 --> 00:15:02.660 align:middle line:90%
of each of those things.

00:15:02.660 --> 00:15:04.243 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: We have
an experience of it.

00:15:04.243 --> 00:15:06.050 align:middle line:84%
And the experience
I have of the sun

00:15:06.050 --> 00:15:08.750 align:middle line:84%
is rather like my
druidic ancestors

00:15:08.750 --> 00:15:12.880 align:middle line:84%
did like 5,000 years ago, which
is, it's a thing that comes up

00:15:12.880 --> 00:15:17.904 align:middle line:84%
over the horizon, warms me,
and the land and things grow,

00:15:17.904 --> 00:15:19.070 align:middle line:90%
and then it goes down again.

00:15:19.070 --> 00:15:21.222 align:middle line:84%
And there's something
transcendental about it

00:15:21.222 --> 00:15:22.680 align:middle line:84%
there's something
special about it.

00:15:22.680 --> 00:15:29.230 align:middle line:84%
And in my mystical tradition of
hermetic origin it's a being.

00:15:29.230 --> 00:15:31.710 align:middle line:90%
It's a life force.

00:15:31.710 --> 00:15:34.640 align:middle line:84%
And you could be very
broad about that and just

00:15:34.640 --> 00:15:37.230 align:middle line:84%
say, oh, it's the giver
of life and it's source

00:15:37.230 --> 00:15:39.530 align:middle line:84%
or it's some sort
of divine oracle.

00:15:39.530 --> 00:15:42.940 align:middle line:84%
And you can be a little general
or you can be very specific

00:15:42.940 --> 00:15:47.190 align:middle line:84%
and say, no, it's an agency
of the divine right here.

00:15:47.190 --> 00:15:49.770 align:middle line:84%
And you know, when one
reads this initially

00:15:49.770 --> 00:15:51.550 align:middle line:84%
as a 20-year-old,
you think, well, it's

00:15:51.550 --> 00:15:54.860 align:middle line:84%
figurative, sort of
religious poetry.

00:15:54.860 --> 00:15:56.470 align:middle line:84%
But with each passing
year, I've come

00:15:56.470 --> 00:15:59.250 align:middle line:84%
to regard that more
and more literally

00:15:59.250 --> 00:16:02.417 align:middle line:84%
and think maybe it is an
agent of something special.

00:16:02.417 --> 00:16:04.250 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'm in alignment
with you on that.

00:16:04.250 --> 00:16:05.280 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:16:05.280 --> 00:16:06.970 align:middle line:84%
And then when you
think about it even

00:16:06.970 --> 00:16:12.370 align:middle line:84%
from an experiential and an
inspirational level, just

00:16:12.370 --> 00:16:16.792 align:middle line:84%
speaking of the sun, when
someone has a little pocket

00:16:16.792 --> 00:16:18.250 align:middle line:84%
change and wants
to go on vacation,

00:16:18.250 --> 00:16:19.600 align:middle line:84%
they usually want to go
somewhere where they're

00:16:19.600 --> 00:16:20.700 align:middle line:90%
being bathed in the sun.

00:16:20.700 --> 00:16:23.350 align:middle line:84%
That's a very common
thing, to bathe in the sun.

00:16:23.350 --> 00:16:28.270 align:middle line:84%
We idealize and want
to experience sunsets

00:16:28.270 --> 00:16:29.520 align:middle line:90%
and sunrises.

00:16:29.520 --> 00:16:32.990 align:middle line:84%
These are really big parts
of our internal psyche

00:16:32.990 --> 00:16:35.500 align:middle line:84%
that goes far beyond
growing plants.

00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:37.530 align:middle line:84%
There is something
transcendental

00:16:37.530 --> 00:16:41.480 align:middle line:84%
as an entity, multi-dimensional
entity itself there.

00:16:41.480 --> 00:16:43.570 align:middle line:84%
And so I mean, I'm with
you on the page of that.

00:16:43.570 --> 00:16:46.250 align:middle line:84%
But that's been through
a lot of thinking,

00:16:46.250 --> 00:16:49.950 align:middle line:84%
reflecting, self-experience,
knowledge to come to,

00:16:49.950 --> 00:16:50.970 align:middle line:90%
what is the sun?

00:16:50.970 --> 00:16:51.770 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:16:51.770 --> 00:16:53.760 align:middle line:90%
And it's a great question.

00:16:53.760 --> 00:16:58.870 align:middle line:84%
And in my work and my written
work and the public seminars

00:16:58.870 --> 00:17:01.820 align:middle line:84%
I do-- and I'm doing
another one in September--

00:17:01.820 --> 00:17:05.319 align:middle line:84%
over and over again we
explore the nature of the sun.

00:17:05.319 --> 00:17:06.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:17:06.420 --> 00:17:07.819 align:middle line:90%
Critical to all life.

00:17:07.819 --> 00:17:10.750 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --and its properties
both in a material sense

00:17:10.750 --> 00:17:15.150 align:middle line:84%
but more significantly
in a-- we'll use

00:17:15.150 --> 00:17:19.421 align:middle line:84%
the Victorian word,
in an etheric sense

00:17:19.421 --> 00:17:21.150 align:middle line:90%
are extremely important.

00:17:21.150 --> 00:17:26.740 align:middle line:84%
And in some of the key texts
that I refer my colleagues

00:17:26.740 --> 00:17:33.050 align:middle line:84%
and clients to, such as the
Corpus Hermeticum, I often--

00:17:33.050 --> 00:17:35.480 align:middle line:84%
and maybe also "The
Kybalion" as well,

00:17:35.480 --> 00:17:38.730 align:middle line:84%
this little book by
William Walker Atkinson--

00:17:38.730 --> 00:17:41.670 align:middle line:84%
the sun keeps appearing
in these texts.

00:17:41.670 --> 00:17:45.180 align:middle line:84%
And they call it the
Heavenly Father and stuff.

00:17:45.180 --> 00:17:48.809 align:middle line:84%
And they call it,
you know, the child--

00:17:48.809 --> 00:17:49.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The sun of God.

00:17:49.850 --> 00:17:52.700 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: The sun of God,
the child of the divine.

00:17:52.700 --> 00:17:56.000 align:middle line:84%
And again, initially
you think it's

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:58.010 align:middle line:84%
some sort of figurative
thing and you think, oh,

00:17:58.010 --> 00:18:01.030 align:middle line:84%
it's a spillover of Christian
literature or something.

00:18:01.030 --> 00:18:01.110 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Metaphorical.

00:18:01.110 --> 00:18:02.200 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: I don't think it is.

00:18:02.200 --> 00:18:04.033 align:middle line:84%
I think they're saying,
well, wait a minute.

00:18:04.033 --> 00:18:07.540 align:middle line:84%
It definitely has a
property of a kind of heat

00:18:07.540 --> 00:18:11.770 align:middle line:84%
and it does amazing
electromagnetic radiations

00:18:11.770 --> 00:18:14.730 align:middle line:84%
out that have an effect and
all the wonderful plants

00:18:14.730 --> 00:18:16.890 align:middle line:90%
photosynthesize and everything.

00:18:16.890 --> 00:18:19.260 align:middle line:84%
That's a thing, but
that's a very narrow

00:18:19.260 --> 00:18:20.480 align:middle line:90%
dimensional property of a--

00:18:20.480 --> 00:18:21.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Material only.

00:18:21.180 --> 00:18:23.096 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: There's something
very big going on,

00:18:23.096 --> 00:18:26.730 align:middle line:84%
so what I say to my
clients, basically,

00:18:26.730 --> 00:18:31.700 align:middle line:84%
is that you come in through
it and you go out through it,

00:18:31.700 --> 00:18:35.480 align:middle line:84%
so the sun is sort of
like the entry point

00:18:35.480 --> 00:18:37.370 align:middle line:90%
to the physical world.

00:18:37.370 --> 00:18:39.560 align:middle line:84%
And you can't get
out until you've

00:18:39.560 --> 00:18:43.200 align:middle line:84%
purified yourself enough to
pass back out through it again.

00:18:43.200 --> 00:18:45.560 align:middle line:84%
And so it's the story
of Icarus, you know,

00:18:45.560 --> 00:18:48.650 align:middle line:84%
and you're not ready
because your impurities

00:18:48.650 --> 00:18:50.920 align:middle line:84%
make it impossible for
you to pass through.

00:18:50.920 --> 00:18:56.470 align:middle line:84%
So like an alchemist will purify
a substance in a laboratory

00:18:56.470 --> 00:19:00.840 align:middle line:84%
or in himself before
transformation, so you have

00:19:00.840 --> 00:19:02.000 align:middle line:90%
to to get out through that.

00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:04.170 align:middle line:84%
So when you die, if
you haven't achieved

00:19:04.170 --> 00:19:06.459 align:middle line:84%
a certain level of attainment,
you have to come back--

00:19:06.459 --> 00:19:07.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The path to the moon.

00:19:07.750 --> 00:19:10.030 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --and continue
refining yourself

00:19:10.030 --> 00:19:11.620 align:middle line:84%
and get recycled
through the moon.

00:19:11.620 --> 00:19:12.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:19:12.420 --> 00:19:14.470 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So these are
funny, crazy ideas.

00:19:14.470 --> 00:19:15.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Until you can
ultimately, as you say,

00:19:15.780 --> 00:19:17.260 align:middle line:84%
make that transit
through the sun

00:19:17.260 --> 00:19:18.290 align:middle line:90%
where you have other options.

00:19:18.290 --> 00:19:19.248 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: That's right.

00:19:19.248 --> 00:19:21.096 align:middle line:84%
Where you can make
some major decisions.

00:19:21.096 --> 00:19:21.462 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Hermetic.

00:19:21.462 --> 00:19:23.100 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So back to
that epistemology,

00:19:23.100 --> 00:19:24.040 align:middle line:90%
we'll just round that piece off.

00:19:24.040 --> 00:19:24.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:19:24.840 --> 00:19:27.270 align:middle line:84%
Because just the sun alone,
just what you're saying now,

00:19:27.270 --> 00:19:30.240 align:middle line:84%
that one contemplation,
is that a place

00:19:30.240 --> 00:19:32.030 align:middle line:84%
you would start some
of your students

00:19:32.030 --> 00:19:34.180 align:middle line:84%
into examining
the nature of what

00:19:34.180 --> 00:19:35.890 align:middle line:90%
is true and is not for you?

00:19:35.890 --> 00:19:36.690 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: It is.

00:19:36.690 --> 00:19:42.270 align:middle line:84%
I would say if you're a
student of spirituality, which

00:19:42.270 --> 00:19:45.680 align:middle line:84%
I imagine much of
your audience is,

00:19:45.680 --> 00:19:51.190 align:middle line:84%
and if you're a student of
Western esoteric traditions

00:19:51.190 --> 00:19:54.850 align:middle line:84%
and magical practices, not
in strictly ceremonial ways,

00:19:54.850 --> 00:19:58.340 align:middle line:84%
more in experiential
ways, perhaps,

00:19:58.340 --> 00:20:02.510 align:middle line:84%
in one's self and one's own
life path, a study of the sun,

00:20:02.510 --> 00:20:07.140 align:middle line:84%
I can't think of a better
test and a better exercise

00:20:07.140 --> 00:20:09.350 align:middle line:90%
for an epistemological study.

00:20:09.350 --> 00:20:10.240 align:middle line:90%
What is knowledge?

00:20:10.240 --> 00:20:11.040 align:middle line:90%
How do you know?

00:20:11.040 --> 00:20:11.890 align:middle line:90%
What does it mean?

00:20:11.890 --> 00:20:13.598 align:middle line:84%
So you can literally--
and I've done this

00:20:13.598 --> 00:20:16.800 align:middle line:84%
with people I work with--
set them off for like two

00:20:16.800 --> 00:20:19.990 align:middle line:84%
weeks with a series
of exercises to say,

00:20:19.990 --> 00:20:22.241 align:middle line:84%
create a relationship
with that sun.

00:20:22.241 --> 00:20:23.990 align:middle line:84%
And then in two weeks,
come back and let's

00:20:23.990 --> 00:20:25.440 align:middle line:90%
talk about what happened.

00:20:25.440 --> 00:20:29.120 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly like
a giant 40, 50, 60

00:20:29.120 --> 00:20:31.820 align:middle line:84%
years of knowledge that
that person had prior

00:20:31.820 --> 00:20:36.220 align:middle line:84%
has been reduced to, well,
that was purely-- they call it

00:20:36.220 --> 00:20:39.260 align:middle line:84%
in philosophy a posteriori,
which is knowledge

00:20:39.260 --> 00:20:41.790 align:middle line:84%
sort of after the
fact, and a priori,

00:20:41.790 --> 00:20:44.850 align:middle line:84%
which is knowledge like
say a classic one is

00:20:44.850 --> 00:20:50.650 align:middle line:84%
you know all birds have
wings, you might say.

00:20:50.650 --> 00:20:52.819 align:middle line:84%
And someone would say,
well, that's true, yeah.

00:20:52.819 --> 00:20:54.360 align:middle line:84%
So I don't need to
see all the birds,

00:20:54.360 --> 00:20:56.010 align:middle line:84%
but I can assume
that might be true.

00:20:56.010 --> 00:20:56.810 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:20:56.810 --> 00:20:58.710 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: You start
to then realized

00:20:58.710 --> 00:21:01.530 align:middle line:84%
what you're taking
as belief and then

00:21:01.530 --> 00:21:03.840 align:middle line:84%
to distinguish what you're
having as experience, which

00:21:03.840 --> 00:21:05.330 align:middle line:90%
in mysticism is crucial.

00:21:05.330 --> 00:21:06.130 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:21:06.130 --> 00:21:09.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So you mustn't
ever dispel anything,

00:21:09.200 --> 00:21:12.150 align:middle line:84%
so whether it's parapolitical
things like 9/11

00:21:12.150 --> 00:21:14.790 align:middle line:84%
and Sandy Hook
and San Bernardino

00:21:14.790 --> 00:21:17.762 align:middle line:84%
recently, which is
very, very, very fishy,

00:21:17.762 --> 00:21:20.442 align:middle line:84%
but you can't go to
YouTube and oh, it's a hoax

00:21:20.442 --> 00:21:21.400 align:middle line:90%
and it's this and that.

00:21:21.400 --> 00:21:22.790 align:middle line:90%
Those people are hopeless.

00:21:22.790 --> 00:21:24.110 align:middle line:90%
They don't know anything.

00:21:24.110 --> 00:21:25.750 align:middle line:84%
And you can't go to
the mainstream news

00:21:25.750 --> 00:21:28.800 align:middle line:84%
and they say, oh, it's these
terrible Islamist people who

00:21:28.800 --> 00:21:32.230 align:middle line:84%
are disgruntled and want
to hurt the Westerners.

00:21:32.230 --> 00:21:35.430 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't seem to be
quite the thing either.

00:21:35.430 --> 00:21:36.810 align:middle line:90%
There's something else.

00:21:36.810 --> 00:21:39.260 align:middle line:84%
And there's no reason
why you can't go and take

00:21:39.260 --> 00:21:41.720 align:middle line:84%
a look at that as
your own study.

00:21:41.720 --> 00:21:44.170 align:middle line:84%
For me, those things
are not as interesting.

00:21:44.170 --> 00:21:47.330 align:middle line:84%
What's more interesting
is the elements, the sun,

00:21:47.330 --> 00:21:51.640 align:middle line:84%
the moon, the Earth, the sky,
even the shape of the world,

00:21:51.640 --> 00:21:52.780 align:middle line:90%
like very--

00:21:52.780 --> 00:21:54.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is a
big one right now.

00:21:54.020 --> 00:21:55.603 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: This is a
big one right now.

00:21:55.603 --> 00:21:57.390 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The flat earth theory.

00:21:57.390 --> 00:22:00.300 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: The idea that it
isn't necessarily a sphere,

00:22:00.300 --> 00:22:01.200 align:middle line:90%
which it isn't.

00:22:01.200 --> 00:22:03.080 align:middle line:84%
It's an oblate
spheroid, for starters.

00:22:03.080 --> 00:22:04.830 align:middle line:84%
Like an orange, if
you do that with it,

00:22:04.830 --> 00:22:06.163 align:middle line:90%
that's actually the shape of it.

00:22:06.163 --> 00:22:07.376 align:middle line:90%
So it isn't a sphere anyway.

00:22:07.376 --> 00:22:11.130 align:middle line:84%
But using our experiential
things-- I mean,

00:22:11.130 --> 00:22:12.470 align:middle line:90%
I just came here.

00:22:12.470 --> 00:22:16.050 align:middle line:84%
We had some weather
yesterday so they went up

00:22:16.050 --> 00:22:19.910 align:middle line:84%
to like 42,000 feet,
which is quite high.

00:22:19.910 --> 00:22:21.290 align:middle line:90%
And the horizon is at eye level.

00:22:21.290 --> 00:22:22.670 align:middle line:90%
It didn't go down.

00:22:22.670 --> 00:22:24.090 align:middle line:90%
And it's perfectly flat.

00:22:24.090 --> 00:22:26.840 align:middle line:90%
It didn't curve at all.

00:22:26.840 --> 00:22:28.820 align:middle line:84%
So that's an
experiential observation.

00:22:28.820 --> 00:22:30.660 align:middle line:84%
I'm not drawing any
conclusions from that.

00:22:30.660 --> 00:22:32.462 align:middle line:90%
I'm just saying.

00:22:32.462 --> 00:22:34.920 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You're putting your
critical faculties and powers

00:22:34.920 --> 00:22:35.992 align:middle line:90%
of observation to work.

00:22:35.992 --> 00:22:36.230 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:22:36.230 --> 00:22:37.390 align:middle line:90%
I'm just taking a look at it.

00:22:37.390 --> 00:22:38.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Taking a look at it.

00:22:38.640 --> 00:22:40.590 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: My friend who
is very scientifically

00:22:40.590 --> 00:22:43.340 align:middle line:84%
minded, originally
from Cambridge,

00:22:43.340 --> 00:22:48.060 align:middle line:84%
he got a laser measurer
from two lighthouse points

00:22:48.060 --> 00:22:52.720 align:middle line:84%
on a stretch of
coastland and measured

00:22:52.720 --> 00:22:56.400 align:middle line:84%
the surface of the water and
there was no curvature at all.

00:22:56.400 --> 00:22:57.200 align:middle line:90%
None.

00:22:57.200 --> 00:22:58.593 align:middle line:90%
Not at all.

00:22:58.593 --> 00:22:59.460 align:middle line:90%
None.

00:22:59.460 --> 00:23:01.400 align:middle line:90%
And he was like, wait a minute.

00:23:01.400 --> 00:23:02.936 align:middle line:90%
That can't be.

00:23:02.936 --> 00:23:07.890 align:middle line:84%
So just in our own little
kind of amateur experiential

00:23:07.890 --> 00:23:09.760 align:middle line:90%
mappings and experiments--

00:23:09.760 --> 00:23:11.385 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This brings
a lot hot debate,

00:23:11.385 --> 00:23:13.642 align:middle line:84%
by the way, a lot-- a lot
of people are looking at it.

00:23:13.642 --> 00:23:15.850 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So you come back
to it and say, well, we'll

00:23:15.850 --> 00:23:16.850 align:middle line:90%
use this as an exercise.

00:23:16.850 --> 00:23:18.460 align:middle line:90%
We're not saying anything.

00:23:18.460 --> 00:23:21.200 align:middle line:84%
What's more interesting to
me than the shape of it,

00:23:21.200 --> 00:23:23.620 align:middle line:84%
because, you know, it would
be a surprise, wouldn't it,

00:23:23.620 --> 00:23:26.390 align:middle line:84%
if it wasn't round,
it is the idea

00:23:26.390 --> 00:23:29.870 align:middle line:90%
of heliocentric and geocentric.

00:23:29.870 --> 00:23:31.350 align:middle line:84%
So heliocentric,
of course, where

00:23:31.350 --> 00:23:34.390 align:middle line:84%
it goes around the sun, and
geocentric, where everything

00:23:34.390 --> 00:23:36.020 align:middle line:90%
goes around the Earth.

00:23:36.020 --> 00:23:40.080 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's experience on Earth
is a geocentric experience.

00:23:40.080 --> 00:23:43.280 align:middle line:84%
No one experiences a
heliocentric sky, do they?

00:23:43.280 --> 00:23:44.090 align:middle line:90%
We're on Earth.

00:23:44.090 --> 00:23:45.320 align:middle line:90%
Things go around us.

00:23:45.320 --> 00:23:46.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
our perspective,

00:23:46.040 --> 00:23:47.200 align:middle line:90%
being on this planet, of course.

00:23:47.200 --> 00:23:48.990 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Everybody's
experience is geocentric.

00:23:48.990 --> 00:23:49.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:23:49.380 --> 00:23:49.980 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:23:49.980 --> 00:23:52.479 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Again, if you go to
the "Corpus Hermeticum," which

00:23:52.479 --> 00:23:55.400 align:middle line:84%
is not the ultimate
text or anything,

00:23:55.400 --> 00:23:59.140 align:middle line:84%
but has more wisdom than any
other text I've ever seen,

00:23:59.140 --> 00:24:01.510 align:middle line:84%
they constantly make
references to the Earth

00:24:01.510 --> 00:24:06.570 align:middle line:84%
being at the center and
to a geocentric model,

00:24:06.570 --> 00:24:10.750 align:middle line:84%
even when they knew there
were other possibilities.

00:24:10.750 --> 00:24:16.030 align:middle line:84%
And again, initially I thought,
well, that's crazy talk.

00:24:16.030 --> 00:24:19.010 align:middle line:84%
People like Galileo
and Bruno had all kinds

00:24:19.010 --> 00:24:23.290 align:middle line:84%
of sticky hands making the
point of it's heliocentric

00:24:23.290 --> 00:24:24.630 align:middle line:90%
and we're like the third.

00:24:24.630 --> 00:24:26.370 align:middle line:84%
There's Mercury,
Venus, Earth, Mars.

00:24:26.370 --> 00:24:27.025 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Third
rock from the sun.

00:24:27.025 --> 00:24:27.825 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: All that.

00:24:27.825 --> 00:24:29.170 align:middle line:90%
Third rock from the sun.

00:24:29.170 --> 00:24:32.270 align:middle line:84%
And yet there's an
insistence-- and the wise men

00:24:32.270 --> 00:24:37.140 align:middle line:84%
that I studied with when I was
a young man in my 20s said,

00:24:37.140 --> 00:24:40.580 align:middle line:84%
don't throw out the idea
of a geocentric model.

00:24:40.580 --> 00:24:42.390 align:middle line:84%
I won't say anymore,
they said to me,

00:24:42.390 --> 00:24:43.960 align:middle line:90%
but don't throw that out.

00:24:43.960 --> 00:24:46.640 align:middle line:84%
It seems crazy, but
don't throw it out.

00:24:46.640 --> 00:24:49.660 align:middle line:84%
Again as an exercise,
I have no idea.

00:24:49.660 --> 00:24:51.900 align:middle line:84%
What I'd like to do is get
in a balloon, you know,

00:24:51.900 --> 00:24:54.340 align:middle line:84%
a space balloon, and
just go up and up and up

00:24:54.340 --> 00:24:56.581 align:middle line:90%
until I can see the ball.

00:24:56.581 --> 00:24:58.080 align:middle line:84%
That would be-- I'd
love to do that.

00:24:58.080 --> 00:24:58.310 align:middle line:90%
That would be interesting.

00:24:58.310 --> 00:24:58.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But the
point is you've

00:24:58.980 --> 00:25:01.634 align:middle line:84%
opened your mind to challenging
the prevailing belief.

00:25:01.634 --> 00:25:03.050 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: I don't
mind if somebody

00:25:03.050 --> 00:25:05.100 align:middle line:90%
says, OK, come in my rocket.

00:25:05.100 --> 00:25:07.050 align:middle line:90%
We're going to fly out.

00:25:07.050 --> 00:25:07.850 align:middle line:90%
You can see it.

00:25:07.850 --> 00:25:09.590 align:middle line:84%
It's a big blue sphere
and come back and be fine.

00:25:09.590 --> 00:25:10.670 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:25:10.670 --> 00:25:11.500 align:middle line:90%
That's fine.

00:25:11.500 --> 00:25:14.100 align:middle line:84%
And if I came out and it
wasn't that, that's fine.

00:25:14.100 --> 00:25:18.060 align:middle line:84%
So when you lead with the
experiential acquisition

00:25:18.060 --> 00:25:21.260 align:middle line:84%
of knowledge, your
agility in not

00:25:21.260 --> 00:25:26.886 align:middle line:84%
having to stick to one
theory is greatly improved.

00:25:26.886 --> 00:25:28.260 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let
me ask you this.

00:25:28.260 --> 00:25:32.580 align:middle line:84%
Then in living anywhere within
the universe or universes,

00:25:32.580 --> 00:25:34.700 align:middle line:84%
on any planet with
whatever culture,

00:25:34.700 --> 00:25:38.720 align:middle line:84%
there are collectively agreed
upon realities which forms

00:25:38.720 --> 00:25:40.990 align:middle line:90%
kind of a baseline of function.

00:25:40.990 --> 00:25:47.380 align:middle line:84%
And how does what you're talking
about interface with that?

00:25:47.380 --> 00:25:49.560 align:middle line:84%
And that's just
for pure function.

00:25:49.560 --> 00:25:50.360 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:25:50.360 --> 00:25:57.660 align:middle line:84%
So consensus reality
is not as important

00:25:57.660 --> 00:26:00.004 align:middle line:90%
in my mystical method.

00:26:00.004 --> 00:26:01.670 align:middle line:84%
I'm not talking about
my historical one.

00:26:01.670 --> 00:26:05.490 align:middle line:84%
I mean what I do now as
my cosmology and my method

00:26:05.490 --> 00:26:09.680 align:middle line:84%
and my practice that people
come to me to learn about.

00:26:09.680 --> 00:26:12.320 align:middle line:84%
The individual is
supreme, right?

00:26:12.320 --> 00:26:13.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:26:13.120 --> 00:26:16.670 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So there is no
objective consensus reality.

00:26:16.670 --> 00:26:20.780 align:middle line:84%
All there is these intertwined
subjective reality tunnels

00:26:20.780 --> 00:26:22.120 align:middle line:90%
that intersect.

00:26:22.120 --> 00:26:23.640 align:middle line:84%
And at intersection
points there's

00:26:23.640 --> 00:26:27.580 align:middle line:84%
great agreement and great
fidelity and definition.

00:26:27.580 --> 00:26:30.750 align:middle line:84%
But there is no one
underlying experience.

00:26:30.750 --> 00:26:32.620 align:middle line:84%
There's also the
other aspect which

00:26:32.620 --> 00:26:34.330 align:middle line:84%
comes very heavily
to this, which

00:26:34.330 --> 00:26:40.870 align:middle line:84%
is a hermetic axiom, which
is in Hermetism they often

00:26:40.870 --> 00:26:44.320 align:middle line:84%
refer to the world as
the all, like everything,

00:26:44.320 --> 00:26:45.890 align:middle line:90%
everythingness.

00:26:45.890 --> 00:26:49.630 align:middle line:84%
And the all is described
as mental, of the mind.

00:26:49.630 --> 00:26:53.000 align:middle line:84%
And so I often will
say it like this.

00:26:53.000 --> 00:26:54.190 align:middle line:90%
The world is a thought.

00:26:54.190 --> 00:26:55.030 align:middle line:90%
It's not a thing.

00:26:55.030 --> 00:27:01.690 align:middle line:84%
It's a thought, because again in
much theology and epistemology

00:27:01.690 --> 00:27:05.280 align:middle line:84%
you'll come across the idea
if the all is everything

00:27:05.280 --> 00:27:09.740 align:middle line:84%
and it's infinite, it can't
be added to or divided.

00:27:09.740 --> 00:27:10.820 align:middle line:90%
It can't be subtracted.

00:27:10.820 --> 00:27:11.930 align:middle line:90%
It can't be cut.

00:27:11.930 --> 00:27:12.870 align:middle line:90%
It can't be unmade.

00:27:12.870 --> 00:27:14.070 align:middle line:90%
It can't be diminished.

00:27:14.070 --> 00:27:16.540 align:middle line:84%
So how can a world
be made within that?

00:27:16.540 --> 00:27:18.730 align:middle line:90%
And this isn't the all.

00:27:18.730 --> 00:27:22.444 align:middle line:84%
This is something else,
because if it was the all,

00:27:22.444 --> 00:27:24.860 align:middle line:84%
it wouldn't diminish because
it's always diminishing this.

00:27:24.860 --> 00:27:27.030 align:middle line:84%
Everything moves
to its end here.

00:27:27.030 --> 00:27:29.520 align:middle line:84%
So there's this fundamental
problem in Hermetism

00:27:29.520 --> 00:27:32.570 align:middle line:84%
which is, OK, so the
world isn't divine,

00:27:32.570 --> 00:27:33.710 align:middle line:90%
and yet it's of the divine.

00:27:33.710 --> 00:27:34.810 align:middle line:90%
How can that be?

00:27:34.810 --> 00:27:36.560 align:middle line:84%
And there's one solution
to that, which is

00:27:36.560 --> 00:27:38.220 align:middle line:90%
it's a thought of the divine.

00:27:38.220 --> 00:27:39.020 align:middle line:90%
It's not a thing.

00:27:39.020 --> 00:27:40.520 align:middle line:90%
It's a thought.

00:27:40.520 --> 00:27:43.950 align:middle line:84%
So this is a dream
of a divine agency.

00:27:43.950 --> 00:27:44.815 align:middle line:90%
And within that--

00:27:44.815 --> 00:27:45.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: A dream/creation.

00:27:45.940 --> 00:27:46.670 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:27:46.670 --> 00:27:47.711 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Creation, yeah.

00:27:47.711 --> 00:27:51.440 align:middle line:84%
And within that,
everybody's personal thought

00:27:51.440 --> 00:27:52.940 align:middle line:90%
feeds into the nature of this.

00:27:52.940 --> 00:27:53.815 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:27:53.815 --> 00:27:58.696 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So the all comes
through humans as conduits

00:27:58.696 --> 00:28:03.470 align:middle line:84%
