>>KRAMER: And we'll go
back to what we started

00:40:01.366 --> 00:40:03.260 align:middle line:90%
at the top of the conversation.

00:40:03.260 --> 00:40:05.800 align:middle line:84%
Even if this is just
an exercise in thought,

00:40:05.800 --> 00:40:11.080 align:middle line:84%
even if this is all poppycock,
fantasy, it's still a good idea

00:40:11.080 --> 00:40:14.180 align:middle line:90%
and that could be the case.

00:40:14.180 --> 00:40:16.940 align:middle line:84%
And it would be rather good
to me if that was the case.

00:40:16.940 --> 00:40:21.760 align:middle line:84%
And I think personally in my
experience, very subjective,

00:40:21.760 --> 00:40:27.230 align:middle line:84%
I have lots of personal--
I hesitate to use the word

00:40:27.230 --> 00:40:29.710 align:middle line:84%
evidence, you know,
underpinnings--

00:40:29.710 --> 00:40:31.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Empirical evidence?

00:40:31.210 --> 00:40:32.870 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: I don't know.

00:40:32.870 --> 00:40:35.870 align:middle line:84%
Proofs for me that have
satisfied me to think,

00:40:35.870 --> 00:40:38.150 align:middle line:90%
I think that is the case.

00:40:38.150 --> 00:40:40.320 align:middle line:84%
You can't really transmit
them, and I never

00:40:40.320 --> 00:40:44.380 align:middle line:84%
care to prove anything or
evidence stuff to people.

00:40:44.380 --> 00:40:47.160 align:middle line:84%
So when they say, well,
how can you say that?

00:40:47.160 --> 00:40:50.456 align:middle line:84%
I can say whatever I want and
I'm not-- I don't give a--

00:40:50.456 --> 00:40:51.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: A rat's tail.

00:40:51.680 --> 00:40:54.804 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --a rat's tail to
evidence or prove anything.

00:40:54.804 --> 00:40:56.220 align:middle line:84%
You know, that's
why I could never

00:40:56.220 --> 00:40:57.970 align:middle line:90%
be an academic philosopher.

00:40:57.970 --> 00:40:59.547 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:40:59.547 --> 00:41:00.630 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: I don't compete.

00:41:00.630 --> 00:41:01.500 align:middle line:90%
I don't argue.

00:41:01.500 --> 00:41:02.300 align:middle line:90%
I don't debate.

00:41:02.300 --> 00:41:05.560 align:middle line:84%
I just say, here's
my worldview and see

00:41:05.560 --> 00:41:07.565 align:middle line:84%
if you find anything
interesting in that,

00:41:07.565 --> 00:41:08.910 align:middle line:90%
and anyway I'm off now.

00:41:08.910 --> 00:41:11.110 align:middle line:84%
I'm on another little
journey somewhere.

00:41:11.110 --> 00:41:16.470 align:middle line:84%
So for me on my little
journeys, I've definitely seen--

00:41:16.470 --> 00:41:21.040 align:middle line:84%
and I think anybody who hand on
heart would examine this point,

00:41:21.040 --> 00:41:23.430 align:middle line:84%
there's clearly different
kinds of humans.

00:41:23.430 --> 00:41:27.319 align:middle line:84%
And it seems to me that
that's OK and natural.

00:41:27.319 --> 00:41:28.860 align:middle line:84%
It's not like there's
dead people who

00:41:28.860 --> 00:41:32.420 align:middle line:84%
are aliens and walk-ins from
other-- I don't mean that.

00:41:32.420 --> 00:41:33.670 align:middle line:90%
I mean they're all legitimate.

00:41:33.670 --> 00:41:34.700 align:middle line:90%
They're all real.

00:41:34.700 --> 00:41:35.740 align:middle line:90%
They're all here.

00:41:35.740 --> 00:41:38.695 align:middle line:84%
We all have the same genetics
and biology and that.

00:41:38.695 --> 00:41:41.730 align:middle line:84%
But the continuance
of that life form

00:41:41.730 --> 00:41:45.165 align:middle line:84%
is radically different
from one to the next.

00:41:45.165 --> 00:41:46.040 align:middle line:90%
Walk down the street.

00:41:46.040 --> 00:41:47.050 align:middle line:90%
You see it every day.

00:41:47.050 --> 00:41:48.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it would seem.

00:41:48.850 --> 00:41:51.370 align:middle line:90%


00:41:51.370 --> 00:41:52.170 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:41:52.170 --> 00:41:55.030 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's a
brave one for people

00:41:55.030 --> 00:41:56.420 align:middle line:90%
to undertake in terms of--

00:41:56.420 --> 00:41:56.654 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:41:56.654 --> 00:41:56.890 align:middle line:90%
How exciting?

00:41:56.890 --> 00:41:58.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --their own
study for what's real.

00:41:58.760 --> 00:41:59.000 align:middle line:90%
God,

00:41:59.000 --> 00:41:59.670 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: How exciting.

00:41:59.670 --> 00:42:01.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Another one,
the sun and the soul force

00:42:01.720 --> 00:42:05.950 align:middle line:84%
of the human species, the
nature of the soul force or not

00:42:05.950 --> 00:42:06.880 align:middle line:90%
of the human species.

00:42:06.880 --> 00:42:08.400 align:middle line:90%
We have two exercises.

00:42:08.400 --> 00:42:10.300 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about depolarization.

00:42:10.300 --> 00:42:11.800 align:middle line:90%
This is one of the things.

00:42:11.800 --> 00:42:14.380 align:middle line:84%
You say what are your
thoughts on-- OK,

00:42:14.380 --> 00:42:16.965 align:middle line:84%
it's collapsing
into the polarity

00:42:16.965 --> 00:42:19.360 align:middle line:90%
and to the center point.

00:42:19.360 --> 00:42:22.430 align:middle line:84%
So right now we're living
in a highly polarized world

00:42:22.430 --> 00:42:23.390 align:middle line:90%
on every level.

00:42:23.390 --> 00:42:24.520 align:middle line:90%
Nature is polarized.

00:42:24.520 --> 00:42:26.200 align:middle line:90%
The universe is polarized.

00:42:26.200 --> 00:42:29.450 align:middle line:84%
Every single atom in
the body is polarized.

00:42:29.450 --> 00:42:32.812 align:middle line:84%
So polarization is
natural state of being.

00:42:32.812 --> 00:42:34.270 align:middle line:84%
But you're speaking
about something

00:42:34.270 --> 00:42:37.960 align:middle line:84%
distinctly different in
collapsing the poles.

00:42:37.960 --> 00:42:41.780 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So polarization
is a mystical principle.

00:42:41.780 --> 00:42:47.690 align:middle line:84%
There's different ones of
rhythm and gender, mentalism

00:42:47.690 --> 00:42:50.130 align:middle line:84%
in the sense of
mind and polarity.

00:42:50.130 --> 00:42:52.970 align:middle line:84%
So everything has its pairs
of opposites that contrast,

00:42:52.970 --> 00:42:53.770 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:42:53.770 --> 00:42:56.090 align:middle line:84%
Hot and cold, life and death,
hard and soft, whatever.

00:42:56.090 --> 00:42:57.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And life's
in the balance point.

00:42:57.840 --> 00:42:58.640 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Right.

00:42:58.640 --> 00:43:03.250 align:middle line:84%
So the idea is that in the
current world iteration,

00:43:03.250 --> 00:43:06.435 align:middle line:84%
in the current
world age, polarity

00:43:06.435 --> 00:43:09.390 align:middle line:84%
is one of its chief
characteristic teaching

00:43:09.390 --> 00:43:10.976 align:middle line:90%
mechanisms.

00:43:10.976 --> 00:43:13.060 align:middle line:84%
And I think I might have
even said this to you

00:43:13.060 --> 00:43:15.610 align:middle line:84%
before in this
studio, but you know,

00:43:15.610 --> 00:43:18.650 align:middle line:84%
the bad polarizations at
the moment are really bad.

00:43:18.650 --> 00:43:20.560 align:middle line:84%
And the good ones
are really good,

00:43:20.560 --> 00:43:23.020 align:middle line:84%
so there's more incredibly
wonderful things happening now

00:43:23.020 --> 00:43:25.830 align:middle line:84%
I think than there have
been for thousands of years,

00:43:25.830 --> 00:43:27.080 align:middle line:90%
and bad things as well.

00:43:27.080 --> 00:43:29.820 align:middle line:84%
So they extend
outwards like this,

00:43:29.820 --> 00:43:31.840 align:middle line:84%
and as they get
more extreme, it's

00:43:31.840 --> 00:43:36.400 align:middle line:84%
a sign of an imminent,
well, reconciliation,

00:43:36.400 --> 00:43:40.330 align:middle line:84%
or if you want a more dramatic
word collapse of polarization.

00:43:40.330 --> 00:43:43.960 align:middle line:84%
Another maxim in my method
is that the point of wisdom

00:43:43.960 --> 00:43:46.240 align:middle line:90%
is only ever the center point.

00:43:46.240 --> 00:43:51.440 align:middle line:84%
So if you know great joy and
great sorrow, only then can you

00:43:51.440 --> 00:43:56.440 align:middle line:84%
find the center point, so by
Point A and Point B, then, OK,

00:43:56.440 --> 00:44:00.580 align:middle line:84%
now I can calculate Point
C in the middle, which

00:44:00.580 --> 00:44:03.340 align:middle line:84%
is a point now where
I can choose when it's

00:44:03.340 --> 00:44:07.210 align:middle line:84%
appropriate to lose
myself, enjoy, and abandon,

00:44:07.210 --> 00:44:14.150 align:middle line:84%
and wonderful wildness, and when
it's time to look at suffering

00:44:14.150 --> 00:44:18.440 align:middle line:84%
and to not be afraid to
feel pain and to see what

00:44:18.440 --> 00:44:20.540 align:middle line:90%
is the purpose of sorrow.

00:44:20.540 --> 00:44:24.200 align:middle line:84%
And a wise man, a wise woman
must be able to do that.

00:44:24.200 --> 00:44:29.560 align:middle line:84%
So it means you have to map
the extremes of both polarities

00:44:29.560 --> 00:44:31.460 align:middle line:90%
to find that center point.

00:44:31.460 --> 00:44:35.970 align:middle line:84%
Again, great disadvantage
in the New Age paradigm

00:44:35.970 --> 00:44:40.190 align:middle line:84%
is that there's a distinct
tendency in gravitation

00:44:40.190 --> 00:44:43.670 align:middle line:84%
to the positive, which is
a disaster, because if you

00:44:43.670 --> 00:44:46.970 align:middle line:84%
miss the negative out, you can't
calculate the center point.

00:44:46.970 --> 00:44:49.320 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of like,
I don't do negative,

00:44:49.320 --> 00:44:52.620 align:middle line:84%
I always think positive,
everything's wonderful.

00:44:52.620 --> 00:44:54.790 align:middle line:84%
People say it's all good
all the time, don't they?

00:44:54.790 --> 00:44:55.730 align:middle line:90%
It's all good.

00:44:55.730 --> 00:44:56.530 align:middle line:90%
Everything's fine.

00:44:56.530 --> 00:44:58.380 align:middle line:90%
It'll all work out OK.

00:44:58.380 --> 00:45:02.490 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going with the flow
and it will be what it will be.

00:45:02.490 --> 00:45:06.640 align:middle line:84%
This moves somebody only to
one end of the spectrum, which

00:45:06.640 --> 00:45:08.190 align:middle line:90%
ignores the other end.

00:45:08.190 --> 00:45:11.790 align:middle line:84%
So you are always going to
trap yourself in polarity

00:45:11.790 --> 00:45:12.840 align:middle line:90%
if you do that.

00:45:12.840 --> 00:45:18.250 align:middle line:84%
So in the work
that I do, we have

00:45:18.250 --> 00:45:23.600 align:middle line:84%
this phrase, invite pain to tea,
just as you would invite joy

00:45:23.600 --> 00:45:24.980 align:middle line:90%
to dinner or whatever.

00:45:24.980 --> 00:45:27.720 align:middle line:84%
You're never afraid to
look at those things.

00:45:27.720 --> 00:45:29.200 align:middle line:90%
So that's in a personal sense.

00:45:29.200 --> 00:45:33.630 align:middle line:84%
In a broader sense,
here's a little bit

00:45:33.630 --> 00:45:36.380 align:middle line:84%
of evidence of how
important this principle is.

00:45:36.380 --> 00:45:38.750 align:middle line:84%
If you look at the
television-- which

00:45:38.750 --> 00:45:41.570 align:middle line:90%
most people are very selective.

00:45:41.570 --> 00:45:43.270 align:middle line:84%
To watch a show
like this, they'll

00:45:43.270 --> 00:45:44.370 align:middle line:90%
come and watch that show.

00:45:44.370 --> 00:45:48.470 align:middle line:84%
I don't think people just sit
down and watch live broadcast

00:45:48.470 --> 00:45:50.440 align:middle line:90%
BBC, CNN, so much or whatever.

00:45:50.440 --> 00:45:53.450 align:middle line:84%
But if you watch
television or newspapers

00:45:53.450 --> 00:45:55.850 align:middle line:84%
and get your things
on your device

00:45:55.850 --> 00:46:00.570 align:middle line:84%
and look at the web pages,
it's compelling all people

00:46:00.570 --> 00:46:01.596 align:middle line:90%
to polarize.

