sell point.

00:46:42.770 --> 00:46:45.080 align:middle line:84%
You have to have an
extreme polarization

00:46:45.080 --> 00:46:47.420 align:middle line:84%
to identify a market to
sell to, which is what

00:46:47.420 --> 00:46:48.990 align:middle line:90%
drives the media to begin with.

00:46:48.990 --> 00:46:50.900 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: You can't get
more polarized really

00:46:50.900 --> 00:46:53.100 align:middle line:84%
than Donald Trump
and Bernie Sanders

00:46:53.100 --> 00:46:56.770 align:middle line:84%
as like a kind of
brash capitalist

00:46:56.770 --> 00:46:58.540 align:middle line:90%
and a kind of geeky Socialist.

00:46:58.540 --> 00:46:59.890 align:middle line:90%
You can't get more polarized.

00:46:59.890 --> 00:47:00.691 align:middle line:90%
And yet--

00:47:00.691 --> 00:47:02.065 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It works
as cover boys.

00:47:02.065 --> 00:47:03.450 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Wrong answers, right?

00:47:03.450 --> 00:47:06.120 align:middle line:84%
That's not going to help
anybody in this society.

00:47:06.120 --> 00:47:08.120 align:middle line:84%
You know, decent guys or
whatever, I don't know.

00:47:08.120 --> 00:47:09.744 align:middle line:84%
Maybe if you went
for dinner with them,

00:47:09.744 --> 00:47:12.530 align:middle line:84%
you'd think, you know, actually
nice people, interesting,

00:47:12.530 --> 00:47:13.710 align:middle line:90%
not quite what I thought.

00:47:13.710 --> 00:47:14.510 align:middle line:90%
Who knows?

00:47:14.510 --> 00:47:16.340 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:47:16.340 --> 00:47:19.900 align:middle line:84%
In what they put forward
it's purposefully polarized.

00:47:19.900 --> 00:47:22.170 align:middle line:84%
And the people who are
pushing that agenda, all

00:47:22.170 --> 00:47:24.480 align:middle line:84%
they have to do is let
that person come forward,

00:47:24.480 --> 00:47:26.480 align:middle line:84%
because Bernie is going
to try and do it anyway.

00:47:26.480 --> 00:47:28.150 align:middle line:84%
Donald's going to
try and do it anyway.

00:47:28.150 --> 00:47:31.150 align:middle line:84%
But people let that happen,
you know, mess with the numbers

00:47:31.150 --> 00:47:32.960 align:middle line:90%
to allow them to rise up.

00:47:32.960 --> 00:47:36.490 align:middle line:84%
So people get the sense
that America is greatly

00:47:36.490 --> 00:47:38.000 align:middle line:90%
polarized at the moment.

00:47:38.000 --> 00:47:42.290 align:middle line:84%
We want a return to American
traditional exceptionalism

00:47:42.290 --> 00:47:46.020 align:middle line:84%
or this Europeanization
of America.

00:47:46.020 --> 00:47:46.820 align:middle line:90%
Oh, dear.

00:47:46.820 --> 00:47:47.620 align:middle line:90%
Please, no.

00:47:47.620 --> 00:47:49.644 align:middle line:84%
So you don't want
that, trust me.

00:47:49.644 --> 00:47:51.354 align:middle line:90%
But all wrong answers, right?

00:47:51.354 --> 00:47:52.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: All wrong answers.

00:47:52.520 --> 00:47:55.132 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So you can't
get to it from that.

00:47:55.132 --> 00:47:56.590 align:middle line:84%
And what it does
again-- and I know

00:47:56.590 --> 00:48:00.690 align:middle line:84%
we discussed this-- is
it totally disempowers

00:48:00.690 --> 00:48:02.680 align:middle line:84%
the creation of the world
from the individual,

00:48:02.680 --> 00:48:04.763 align:middle line:84%
because you just think,
well, I can't do anything.

00:48:04.763 --> 00:48:07.520 align:middle line:84%
All I can do is
every four years is

00:48:07.520 --> 00:48:10.470 align:middle line:84%
put a ballot in to
vote for somebody,

00:48:10.470 --> 00:48:12.890 align:middle line:84%
or maybe vote locally
every couple of years,

00:48:12.890 --> 00:48:15.610 align:middle line:84%
or maybe write to my
senator or something.

00:48:15.610 --> 00:48:17.380 align:middle line:90%
That's all I can really do.

00:48:17.380 --> 00:48:21.680 align:middle line:84%
And as soon as you get caught up
in that politicization of life,

00:48:21.680 --> 00:48:23.950 align:middle line:84%
you're not creating the
world you want to create.

00:48:23.950 --> 00:48:26.970 align:middle line:84%
You're creating what
you're told to create.

00:48:26.970 --> 00:48:32.940 align:middle line:84%
So in my method, it's much
more like urgent and material

00:48:32.940 --> 00:48:33.740 align:middle line:90%
than you think.

00:48:33.740 --> 00:48:38.710 align:middle line:84%
It's not a principle, a sort
of idealist view of what we

00:48:38.710 --> 00:48:40.970 align:middle line:90%
could do to create a better--

00:48:40.970 --> 00:48:45.080 align:middle line:84%
We create this every single
day we take a breath.

00:48:45.080 --> 00:48:46.480 align:middle line:90%
We're making this.

00:48:46.480 --> 00:48:49.850 align:middle line:84%
And if you're not sure who
you are and what you're doing,

00:48:49.850 --> 00:48:52.930 align:middle line:84%
you end up making what someone
else tells you to make.

00:48:52.930 --> 00:48:55.916 align:middle line:84%
And that polarization
process is designed

00:48:55.916 --> 00:48:57.540 align:middle line:84%
for one thing and
one thing only, which

00:48:57.540 --> 00:49:00.130 align:middle line:84%
is to instruct
human beings to make

00:49:00.130 --> 00:49:02.390 align:middle line:84%
a world that someone else
is instructing them to do,

00:49:02.390 --> 00:49:03.190 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:49:03.190 --> 00:49:05.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:49:05.550 --> 00:49:08.820 align:middle line:84%
For gain, for
whichever gain, you

00:49:08.820 --> 00:49:10.370 align:middle line:84%
know, whether it's
an energetic gain

00:49:10.370 --> 00:49:13.060 align:middle line:84%
or whether it's a material
gain, by those programming

00:49:13.060 --> 00:49:13.930 align:middle line:90%
that reality.

00:49:13.930 --> 00:49:19.150 align:middle line:84%
And as you were talking earlier
about becoming lost in pain

00:49:19.150 --> 00:49:21.640 align:middle line:84%
or becoming lost in
bliss, it doesn't really

00:49:21.640 --> 00:49:23.000 align:middle line:90%
matter which one it is.

00:49:23.000 --> 00:49:25.880 align:middle line:84%
There's a real maturity
and thoughtfulness

00:49:25.880 --> 00:49:29.640 align:middle line:84%
that has to take place to
find one's way to the center

00:49:29.640 --> 00:49:30.880 align:middle line:90%
and employ will.

00:49:30.880 --> 00:49:32.700 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk about
will for a moment.

00:49:32.700 --> 00:49:35.610 align:middle line:84%
This is a misunderstood
word and the thing

00:49:35.610 --> 00:49:38.900 align:middle line:84%
that's probably needed more
than anything right now.

00:49:38.900 --> 00:49:41.670 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So I'll tell
you just straight off,

00:49:41.670 --> 00:49:43.500 align:middle line:90%
will is a divine thing.

00:49:43.500 --> 00:49:48.660 align:middle line:84%
And it's like the
creational imperative that

00:49:48.660 --> 00:49:52.850 align:middle line:84%
is given to the ensouled human
to say, while you're here,

00:49:52.850 --> 00:49:55.710 align:middle line:84%
you can do whatever you wish
with your creational gift.

00:49:55.710 --> 00:49:58.420 align:middle line:84%
You can create a
dreadful dystopia

00:49:58.420 --> 00:50:00.150 align:middle line:90%
or a wonderful paradise.

00:50:00.150 --> 00:50:02.029 align:middle line:84%
You can laugh and
dance or you can

00:50:02.029 --> 00:50:03.820 align:middle line:84%
sit in the corner over
there and, you know,

00:50:03.820 --> 00:50:04.480 align:middle line:90%
slit your wrists.

00:50:04.480 --> 00:50:05.688 align:middle line:90%
You can do whatever you want.

00:50:05.688 --> 00:50:06.980 align:middle line:90%
It's all good.

00:50:06.980 --> 00:50:08.600 align:middle line:84%
But you have the
power to create,

00:50:08.600 --> 00:50:12.830 align:middle line:90%
so will is a divine ordinance.

00:50:12.830 --> 00:50:19.025 align:middle line:84%
And I would say if we want to be
brave in language for a minute,

00:50:19.025 --> 00:50:21.090 align:middle line:90%
it essentially is God's will.

00:50:21.090 --> 00:50:22.720 align:middle line:84%
And I would say
God's a funny word

00:50:22.720 --> 00:50:26.510 align:middle line:84%
to use, in that it is
given to you to say here's

00:50:26.510 --> 00:50:27.720 align:middle line:90%
a piece of my will.

00:50:27.720 --> 00:50:28.520 align:middle line:90%
There you go.

00:50:28.520 --> 00:50:31.850 align:middle line:84%
And while you've got it, you can
do whatever you want with it.

00:50:31.850 --> 00:50:38.840 align:middle line:84%
That will is responsible
for the shape, the texture,

00:50:38.840 --> 00:50:41.850 align:middle line:84%
the tone, the duration
of this world.

00:50:41.850 --> 00:50:45.420 align:middle line:84%
And only people who
choose to exercise it

00:50:45.420 --> 00:50:48.690 align:middle line:84%
can actually manifest
anything at all.

00:50:48.690 --> 00:50:51.030 align:middle line:84%
It can be de-activated,
that will.

00:50:51.030 --> 00:50:54.930 align:middle line:84%
And its most closely
equated thing

00:50:54.930 --> 00:50:57.530 align:middle line:84%
is a sort of loss
of belief or, as you

00:50:57.530 --> 00:50:59.790 align:middle line:84%
say, a kind of
cynicism, where you just

00:50:59.790 --> 00:51:01.290 align:middle line:90%
think, well, what's the point?

00:51:01.290 --> 00:51:02.290 align:middle line:90%
Why bother?

00:51:02.290 --> 00:51:02.870 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:51:02.870 --> 00:51:04.453 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we all have
moments like that,

00:51:04.453 --> 00:51:06.610 align:middle line:84%
but some people go through
decades of why bother?

00:51:06.610 --> 00:51:07.660 align:middle line:90%
There's no point.

00:51:07.660 --> 00:51:10.929 align:middle line:84%
Everything is so hopelessly
broken, why bother?

00:51:10.929 --> 00:51:12.970 align:middle line:84%
You know, there's no point
in getting out of bed.

00:51:12.970 --> 00:51:14.870 align:middle line:84%
We might as well just play
video games or watch old movies

00:51:14.870 --> 00:51:16.220 align:middle line:90%
and eat pizza or whatever.

00:51:16.220 --> 00:51:18.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, we're
seeing the effects of that.

00:51:18.470 --> 00:51:19.270 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Right.

00:51:19.270 --> 00:51:21.650 align:middle line:84%
So you see that, there's
just giant apathy.

00:51:21.650 --> 00:51:23.680 align:middle line:84%
And that's like the
deactivation of will.

00:51:23.680 --> 00:51:29.630 align:middle line:84%
So will is really like a lovely
bestowal, a sort of endowment

00:51:29.630 --> 00:51:32.480 align:middle line:84%
to say, here's a
very beautiful gift

00:51:32.480 --> 00:51:37.130 align:middle line:90%
of great power and great love.

00:51:37.130 --> 00:51:39.336 align:middle line:90%
And you don't have to use it.

00:51:39.336 --> 00:51:41.470 align:middle line:84%
And be careful you don't
get tricked into using it

00:51:41.470 --> 00:51:42.640 align:middle line:90%
for the wrong thing.

00:51:42.640 --> 00:51:45.200 align:middle line:84%
But once you have
it, it is the thing

00:51:45.200 --> 00:51:48.710 align:middle line:84%
that allows you to discern
and judge and discriminate

00:51:48.710 --> 00:51:52.500 align:middle line:84%
in the most excellent
possible senses.

00:51:52.500 --> 00:51:55.930 align:middle line:84%
It enables you to depolarize
and find that center point.

00:51:55.930 --> 00:51:57.890 align:middle line:84%
And once you've mapped
both polarizations,

00:51:57.890 --> 00:52:01.670 align:middle line:84%
you don't need to play that game
anymore like good day, bad day,

00:52:01.670 --> 00:52:02.565 align:middle line:90%
good day.

00:52:02.565 --> 00:52:05.010 align:middle line:84%
Oh, totally in love,
totally despondent.

00:52:05.010 --> 00:52:06.630 align:middle line:90%
That doesn't happen anymore.

00:52:06.630 --> 00:52:08.310 align:middle line:84%
When you've got the
center point, you

00:52:08.310 --> 00:52:11.620 align:middle line:84%
can move with this principle
of rhythm and think,

00:52:11.620 --> 00:52:14.980 align:middle line:84%
OK, well, you know,
melancholy shows us something.

00:52:14.980 --> 00:52:16.470 align:middle line:90%
Loneliness shows you something.

00:52:16.470 --> 00:52:17.745 align:middle line:90%
But it's not going to trap me.

00:52:17.745 --> 00:52:19.620 align:middle line:84%
It's not going to kill
me like it used to do,

00:52:19.620 --> 00:52:21.080 align:middle line:90%
because I've been there.

00:52:21.080 --> 00:52:22.920 align:middle line:84%
And now I don't need
to do that anymore.

00:52:22.920 --> 00:52:25.765 align:middle line:84%
Once you get that center point
consistent and you can sustain

00:52:25.765 --> 00:52:29.590 align:middle line:84%
it, the whole polarization
collapses and pain

00:52:29.590 --> 00:52:31.400 align:middle line:90%
ceases to be pain anymore.

00:52:31.400 --> 00:52:32.610 align:middle line:90%
Joy ceases to be joy.

00:52:32.610 --> 00:52:34.000 align:middle line:90%
It's something else.

00:52:34.000 --> 00:52:35.970 align:middle line:90%
You transcend that whole thing.

00:52:35.970 --> 00:52:39.580 align:middle line:84%
So you might say there's 12
ultimate polarizations, which

00:52:39.580 --> 00:52:41.220 align:middle line:84%
we'll talk about
some other time.

00:52:41.220 --> 00:52:45.070 align:middle line:84%
And part of life coming here is
to learn each one and collapse

00:52:45.070 --> 00:52:47.310 align:middle line:90%
m reconcile it for yourself.

00:52:47.310 --> 00:52:52.240 align:middle line:84%
And when all the people who are
creating this have done that,

00:52:52.240 --> 00:52:53.240 align:middle line:90%
you get an Earth change.

00:52:53.240 --> 00:52:54.830 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And different
reality entirely.

00:52:54.830 --> 00:52:56.371 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: You get
a big Earth change.

00:52:56.371 --> 00:52:58.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: There's this--
now, this is more personal.

00:52:58.540 --> 00:53:03.460 align:middle line:84%
It's just kind of a feeling
more than anything within myself

00:53:03.460 --> 00:53:10.270 align:middle line:84%
is this reemergence of a desire
to see enacted what you would

00:53:10.270 --> 00:53:14.330 align:middle line:84%
call in the most classical
mythical Arthurian terms

00:53:14.330 --> 00:53:16.600 align:middle line:84%
chivalry in its truest
sense of the word.

00:53:16.600 --> 00:53:17.400 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like--

00:53:17.400 --> 00:53:19.580 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: That's a word
you don't hear very much.

00:53:19.580 --> 00:53:21.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's something
I'm looking into,

00:53:21.930 --> 00:53:24.380 align:middle line:84%
I'm studying from ancient and
modern viewpoints right now.

00:53:24.380 --> 00:53:27.780 align:middle line:84%
But the point is that
there's something in myself--

00:53:27.780 --> 00:53:31.030 align:middle line:84%
and when I hear other people
speak, especially women,

00:53:31.030 --> 00:53:36.420 align:middle line:84%
I'm seeing this as a
thing that is being craved

00:53:36.420 --> 00:53:40.590 align:middle line:84%
on a subconscious level, the
truest, purest version of what

00:53:40.590 --> 00:53:41.390 align:middle line:90%
chivalry is.

00:53:41.390 --> 00:53:43.910 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't mean Sir Walter
Raleigh throwing your coat down

00:53:43.910 --> 00:53:45.050 align:middle line:90%
in the mud for a woman.

00:53:45.050 --> 00:53:47.587 align:middle line:84%
No, I mean that will,
that standing up

00:53:47.587 --> 00:53:49.420 align:middle line:84%
for what's right and
truthful and putting it

00:53:49.420 --> 00:53:50.461 align:middle line:90%
all on the line for that.

00:53:50.461 --> 00:53:51.440 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: It is.

00:53:51.440 --> 00:53:54.480 align:middle line:84%
It's honorable conduct,
which is to say

00:53:54.480 --> 00:53:56.790 align:middle line:84%
no when it's unpopular
and yes when it's

00:53:56.790 --> 00:53:58.260 align:middle line:90%
unpopular in equal measure.

00:53:58.260 --> 00:53:59.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:53:59.090 --> 00:54:00.548 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: And to
call it, you know,

00:54:00.548 --> 00:54:06.180 align:middle line:84%
and to like not fall under
the brainwashing of sexism

00:54:06.180 --> 00:54:07.710 align:middle line:90%
or racism or this or that.

00:54:07.710 --> 00:54:12.220 align:middle line:84%
Many of these things, like
I often to say to people

00:54:12.220 --> 00:54:13.970 align:middle line:84%
there is no such
thing as equality.

00:54:13.970 --> 00:54:15.050 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't exist.

00:54:15.050 --> 00:54:16.150 align:middle line:90%
We don't need it.

00:54:16.150 --> 00:54:18.240 align:middle line:84%
There's no equality
in nature, is there?

00:54:18.240 --> 00:54:19.040 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't exist.

00:54:19.040 --> 00:54:20.080 align:middle line:90%
It's not necessary.

00:54:20.080 --> 00:54:21.874 align:middle line:90%
Neither is it here.

00:54:21.874 --> 00:54:23.290 align:middle line:84%
Everything's
completely different.

00:54:23.290 --> 00:54:24.550 align:middle line:90%
There's no need for it.

00:54:24.550 --> 00:54:27.307 align:middle line:84%
You might have equity of
potential, but that's--

00:54:27.307 --> 00:54:28.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's a
good way to put it.

00:54:28.890 --> 00:54:30.380 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: That's
God-given for everybody.

00:54:30.380 --> 00:54:30.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:54:30.750 --> 00:54:32.530 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: And that's
up to you, yourself.

00:54:32.530 --> 00:54:35.610 align:middle line:84%
But equality, you can't go
around an establish that.

00:54:35.610 --> 00:54:39.620 align:middle line:84%
So part of honorable
conduct is to call falsehood

00:54:39.620 --> 00:54:40.532 align:middle line:90%
when you see it.

00:54:40.532 --> 00:54:42.240 align:middle line:84%
So if someone says,
well, obviously Neil,

00:54:42.240 --> 00:54:44.520 align:middle line:84%
we're all working towards
more equality in the world,

00:54:44.520 --> 00:54:46.030 align:middle line:90%
aren't we, no, I'm not.

00:54:46.030 --> 00:54:46.920 align:middle line:90%
I'm not personally.

00:54:46.920 --> 00:54:48.114 align:middle line:90%
No, I'm not.

00:54:48.114 --> 00:54:49.530 align:middle line:84%
And goodness me,
what do you mean?

00:54:49.530 --> 00:54:51.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: There's a level
of personal excellence

00:54:51.840 --> 00:54:54.780 align:middle line:84%
that's embodied in the notion
of chivalry in each of us

00:54:54.780 --> 00:54:58.900 align:middle line:84%
too, which we have let go by
the wayside out of programming

00:54:58.900 --> 00:54:59.700 align:middle line:90%
and laziness.

00:54:59.700 --> 00:55:02.260 align:middle line:84%
This takes strength,
fearlessness, maturity,

00:55:02.260 --> 00:55:04.850 align:middle line:84%
all of these things to
employ will properly.

00:55:04.850 --> 00:55:05.650 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:55:05.650 --> 00:55:06.450 align:middle line:90%
It does.

00:55:06.450 --> 00:55:10.300 align:middle line:84%
And as you say that,
that again uncommon word,

00:55:10.300 --> 00:55:13.032 align:middle line:90%
strength, power, courage.

00:55:13.032 --> 00:55:15.260 align:middle line:84%
You know, those are
like rare things

00:55:15.260 --> 00:55:19.190 align:middle line:84%
that are you might even
say unfashionable nowadays.

00:55:19.190 --> 00:55:21.990 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's much more
fashionable to be we can

00:55:21.990 --> 00:55:24.112 align:middle line:90%
sort of, oh, I don't know and--

00:55:24.112 --> 00:55:25.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think
we've done enough of it

00:55:25.820 --> 00:55:27.400 align:middle line:90%
and it's not working very well.

00:55:27.400 --> 00:55:29.580 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: It doesn't
work very well, you know.

00:55:29.580 --> 00:55:36.090 align:middle line:84%
To see people of conviction
and experience and maturity

00:55:36.090 --> 00:55:39.960 align:middle line:84%
come forward and
share their vision

00:55:39.960 --> 00:55:41.750 align:middle line:84%
of excellence,
personal excellence,

00:55:41.750 --> 00:55:43.209 align:middle line:84%
forget judging it
for other people,

00:55:43.209 --> 00:55:44.250 align:middle line:90%
you can't really do that.

00:55:44.250 --> 00:55:44.376 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:55:44.376 --> 00:55:45.176 align:middle line:90%
Personal.

00:55:45.176 --> 00:55:48.160 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Just for yourself
to say I am going to achieve

00:55:48.160 --> 00:55:51.420 align:middle line:84%
a level of quality in
whatever things I'm doing,

00:55:51.420 --> 00:55:58.140 align:middle line:84%
whether it's cooking dinner
or loving my family or writing

00:55:58.140 --> 00:56:01.670 align:middle line:84%
a book or painting
a picture, a canvas,

00:56:01.670 --> 00:56:06.880 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to achieve a level
of quality that satisfies me

00:56:06.880 --> 00:56:11.590 align:middle line:84%
and really is something that
I can excel in, stand back

00:56:11.590 --> 00:56:14.560 align:middle line:84%
and think, you know, that
is a fine achievement,

00:56:14.560 --> 00:56:17.760 align:middle line:84%
just for me a fine achievement,
and I'm going to strive to keep

00:56:17.760 --> 00:56:21.140 align:middle line:84%
pushing that and pushing it
and having greater levels

00:56:21.140 --> 00:56:24.150 align:middle line:84%
of elegance and effortless
beauty and harmony,

00:56:24.150 --> 00:56:28.070 align:middle line:84%
not like an endeavor like
this, but more like this

00:56:28.070 --> 00:56:32.100 align:middle line:84%
gracefulness-- again a word
you don't hear very much--

00:56:32.100 --> 00:56:35.760 align:middle line:84%
that to me is all
tied up in many

00:56:35.760 --> 00:56:38.746 align:middle line:84%
of the things we talked
about today with will

00:56:38.746 --> 00:56:42.020 align:middle line:84%
and honorable conduct and
courage, individualism.

00:56:42.020 --> 00:56:43.900 align:middle line:90%
They're natural parts of that.

00:56:43.900 --> 00:56:47.860 align:middle line:84%
So again, the empire that
wants to collectivize and say,

00:56:47.860 --> 00:56:49.980 align:middle line:84%
look, don't worry about
individual excellence,

00:56:49.980 --> 00:56:52.990 align:middle line:84%
we should all be about the same,
we should all look the same,

00:56:52.990 --> 00:56:55.270 align:middle line:90%
and we should all be largely--

00:56:55.270 --> 00:56:57.755 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think they tried
that in the Soviet Union

00:56:57.755 --> 00:56:58.210 align:middle line:90%
for a long time.

00:56:58.210 --> 00:56:59.010 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:56:59.010 --> 00:57:02.060 align:middle line:90%
It's just not a human way to be.

00:57:02.060 --> 00:57:07.000 align:middle line:84%
So individualism and will
for me sort of go hand

00:57:07.000 --> 00:57:13.100 align:middle line:84%
in hand, in that you achieve
naturally greater compassion

00:57:13.100 --> 00:57:17.540 align:middle line:84%
and consideration automatically
with maturing selfhood.

00:57:17.540 --> 00:57:18.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:57:18.340 --> 00:57:20.280 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: And so you don't need
to worry about somebody saying,

00:57:20.280 --> 00:57:22.920 align:middle line:84%
well, I'm going to take
part of your annual income

00:57:22.920 --> 00:57:25.210 align:middle line:84%
and give it to these--
well, I'll decide that,

00:57:25.210 --> 00:57:27.780 align:middle line:84%
because that will
naturally occur to me.

00:57:27.780 --> 00:57:29.750 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to
decide that for me.

00:57:29.750 --> 00:57:31.434 align:middle line:84%
And this guy on
the street corner

00:57:31.434 --> 00:57:33.600 align:middle line:84%
who's asking for your money,
and there's another guy

00:57:33.600 --> 00:57:36.800 align:middle line:84%
here, I might look at this guy
and just think, you're a bum.

00:57:36.800 --> 00:57:38.490 align:middle line:90%
You, on the other hand, are not.

00:57:38.490 --> 00:57:40.040 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to
like help you out.

00:57:40.040 --> 00:57:41.310 align:middle line:90%
I'll decide that.

00:57:41.310 --> 00:57:44.086 align:middle line:90%
You can't sort of--

00:57:44.086 --> 00:57:46.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's a sovereignty,
a process of being sovereign.

00:57:46.640 --> 00:57:47.440 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: It is.

00:57:47.440 --> 00:57:48.090 align:middle line:90%
I'll decide that.

00:57:48.090 --> 00:57:48.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:57:48.440 --> 00:57:50.231 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Everyone else
should decide that.

00:57:50.231 --> 00:57:52.280 align:middle line:84%
You can't have that
prescribed for you.

00:57:52.280 --> 00:57:55.420 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's what the
collectivization process

00:57:55.420 --> 00:57:58.620 align:middle line:84%
and empire does,
especially in the sort

00:57:58.620 --> 00:58:00.780 align:middle line:84%
of left-leaning, liberal,
progressive world,

00:58:00.780 --> 00:58:04.470 align:middle line:84%
which is supposed to be cleverer
and more forward-thinking.

00:58:04.470 --> 00:58:07.170 align:middle line:84%
They're really
deceived by this worse

00:58:07.170 --> 00:58:09.110 align:middle line:84%
than the bloody
right-wingers, you know.

00:58:09.110 --> 00:58:12.670 align:middle line:84%
So I don't want to politicize
it, but at each end of it,

00:58:12.670 --> 00:58:18.290 align:middle line:84%
the traditional conservatives,
the modern left-wing liberal

00:58:18.290 --> 00:58:21.410 align:middle line:84%
Democrats, all that
stuff, both wrong answers.

00:58:21.410 --> 00:58:25.420 align:middle line:84%
You have to totally depoliticize
the whole thing and say,

00:58:25.420 --> 00:58:27.810 align:middle line:90%
that's not a real thing.

00:58:27.810 --> 00:58:29.340 align:middle line:90%
People don't really do that.

00:58:29.340 --> 00:58:31.520 align:middle line:84%
The only people who go
to those polarizations

00:58:31.520 --> 00:58:36.150 align:middle line:84%
are people who choose not
to think for themselves.

00:58:36.150 --> 00:58:39.450 align:middle line:84%
In modern mystical
practices I put forward,

00:58:39.450 --> 00:58:43.770 align:middle line:84%
my method and my
examination of this,

00:58:43.770 --> 00:58:47.940 align:middle line:84%
it returns that permission
and that allowance

00:58:47.940 --> 00:58:51.320 align:middle line:84%
and that dignity to
make your own decisions

00:58:51.320 --> 00:58:53.740 align:middle line:84%
and to have that
where you can put

00:58:53.740 --> 00:58:56.060 align:middle line:84%
your head on the pillow
at night and think,

00:58:56.060 --> 00:58:59.430 align:middle line:84%
I did the right thing today
in difficult circumstances

00:58:59.430 --> 00:59:03.800 align:middle line:84%
and I feel some organic,
natural pride about that

00:59:03.800 --> 00:59:06.090 align:middle line:90%
in the best sense of the word.

00:59:06.090 --> 00:59:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And it totally disempowers that
political polarized process

00:59:12.130 --> 00:59:15.770 align:middle line:84%
and people just switching that
off and tiny numbers of voters

00:59:15.770 --> 00:59:16.660 align:middle line:90%
going out, you know.

00:59:16.660 --> 00:59:17.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:59:17.280 --> 00:59:18.080 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:59:18.080 --> 00:59:21.750 align:middle line:84%
Well, that was a
beautiful explanation.

00:59:21.750 --> 00:59:23.410 align:middle line:84%
And we only have a
minute or so left,

00:59:23.410 --> 00:59:24.950 align:middle line:90%
so is there any final thought?

00:59:24.950 --> 00:59:26.445 align:middle line:84%
There are a few
things that I would

00:59:26.445 --> 00:59:27.653 align:middle line:90%
have liked to have gotten to.

00:59:27.653 --> 00:59:31.070 align:middle line:84%
Is there a final
thought you might have?

00:59:31.070 --> 00:59:35.010 align:middle line:10%
>>KRAMER: I would say that in
